Class DialogComponentEnumSelection<T extends java.lang.Enum<T>>

  • java.lang.Object

      • org.rdkit.knime.util.DialogComponentEnumSelection<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - An arbitrary Enumeration.

    public final class DialogComponentEnumSelection<T extends java.lang.Enum<T>>
extends DialogComponent
    Provides a standard component for a dialog that allows to select an enumeration value.
    Author:
    Manuel Schwarze, based on work of Thomas Gabriel, Thomas Gabriel, University of Konstanz

    • Constructor Detail

      • DialogComponentEnumSelection

        @SafeVarargs
public DialogComponentEnumSelection(SettingsModelEnumeration<T> enumModel,
                                                  java.lang.String label,
                                                  T... list)
        Constructor that puts label and combobox into panel. It expects the user to make a selection, thus, at least one item in the list of selectable items is required. When the settings are applied, the model stores one of the enumerations of the provided list.
        Parameters:
        enumModel - The model that stores the value for this component.
        label - Label for dialog in front of combobox
        list - List of items for the combobox. If no list or an empty list is provided all possible values will be taken from the Enumeration used in the settings model.

      • DialogComponentEnumSelection

        public DialogComponentEnumSelection(SettingsModelEnumeration<T> enumModel,

        Constructor that puts label and combobox into panel. It expects the user to make a selection, thus, at least one item in the list of selectable items is required. When the settings are applied, the model stores one of the enumerations of the provided list.
        Parameters:
        enumModel - the model that stores the value for this component.
        label - label for dialog in front of combobox
        list - List of items for the combobox. If no list or an empty list is provided all possible values will be taken from the Enumeration used in the settings model.
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if one of the strings in the list is null

      • DialogComponentEnumSelection

        public DialogComponentEnumSelection(SettingsModelEnumeration<T> enumModel,
                                    java.lang.String label,

        Constructor that puts label and combobox into panel. It expects the user to make a selection, thus, at least one item in the list of selectable items is required. When the settings are applied, the model stores one of the enumerations of the provided list.
        Parameters:
        enumModel - the model that stores the value for this component.
        label - label for dialog in front of combobox
        list - List of items for the combobox. If no list or an empty list is provided all possible values will be taken from the Enumeration used in the settings model.
        fvm - model exposed to choose from available flow variables
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if one of the strings in the list is null
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the list is empty or null.

      • replaceListItems

        public void replaceListItems(java.util.Collection<T> newItems,
                             T select)
        Replaces the list of selectable strings in the component. If select is specified (not null) and it exists in the collection it will be selected. If select is null, the previous value will stay selected (if it exists in the new list).
        Parameters:
        newItems - new strings for the combo box
        select - the item to select after the replace. Can be null, in which case the previous selection remains - if it exists in the new list.
